1
00:00:23,333 --> 00:00:25,041
♪ I THINK IT'S TIME
WE BLOW THIS SCENE. ♪

2
00:00:25,125 --> 00:00:27,875
♪ GET EVERYBODY
AND THEIR STUFF TOGETHER. ♪

3
00:00:27,958 --> 00:00:30,750
♪ OK, 3, 2, 1.
LET'S JAM. ♪

4
00:02:01,291 --> 00:02:03,333
CONFIRMED.

5
00:02:04,458 --> 00:02:08,333
TO THE NEW ALLIANCE,
AND PERHAPS EVEN FRIENDSHIP.

6
00:02:08,416 --> 00:02:10,833
AND TO SUCCESS
FOR BOTH OF US.

7
00:02:10,916 --> 00:02:13,333
I HAD NO IDEA
THE VIEW FROM UP HERE

8
00:02:13,416 --> 00:02:14,708
WOULD BE SO BREATHTAKING.

9
00:02:14,791 --> 00:02:16,416
IT MAKES ME SAD TO LEAVE.

10
00:02:16,500 --> 00:02:19,500
THE NEXT TIME,
YOU'LL HAVE TO STAY FOR DINNER.

11
00:02:19,583 --> 00:02:21,625
OUR CHEF COOKS
A CANTONESE CUISINE

12
00:02:21,708 --> 00:02:24,000
THAT'S JUST AS SUPERB
AS THE SCENERY.

13
00:02:24,083 --> 00:02:26,458
IT'S TO DIE FOR,
SO TO SPEAK.

14
00:02:26,541 --> 00:02:28,708
THAT'S QUITE AN INVITATION.

15
00:02:28,791 --> 00:02:30,666
I NEVER THOUGHT
I'D BREAK BREAD WITH A CAPO

16
00:02:30,750 --> 00:02:33,791
FROM THE RED DRAGON CLAN.

17
00:02:33,875 --> 00:02:34,625
DON'T WORRY.

18
00:02:34,708 --> 00:02:36,291
THE FOOD WON'T BE POISONED.

19
00:02:36,375 --> 00:02:38,541
NO MORE BETRAYALS.

20
00:02:47,208 --> 00:02:52,375
THANK GOD I CAN FINALLY RELAX,
TAKE A LITTLE BREATHER.

21
00:02:59,458 --> 00:03:03,958
[BIRD SQUAWKING]

22
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:09,791
THIS WON'T DO YOU ANY GOOD.

23
00:03:09,875 --> 00:03:11,750
THE TIMES HAVE CHANGED.

24
00:03:11,833 --> 00:03:15,000
THE SYNDICATES CAN'T
SURVIVE LIKE THIS ANY LONGER.

25
00:03:15,083 --> 00:03:19,375
THIS ENDLESS BLOODLETTING
IS TEARING US ALL APART.

26
00:03:22,791 --> 00:03:24,166
[GASPS]

27
00:03:24,250 --> 00:03:30,625
IF SPIKE WERE HERE...
YOU WOULD NEVER HAVE DONE THIS.

28
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:47,291
I DON'T FEEL UP FOR THIS.

29
00:03:47,375 --> 00:03:48,333
[WHINES]

30
00:03:48,416 --> 00:03:49,375
HUH?

31
00:03:49,458 --> 00:03:51,583
I SAID, I DON'T FEEL
LIKE DOING THIS.

32
00:03:51,666 --> 00:03:53,375
THEN I HAVE NO CHOICE.

33
00:03:53,458 --> 00:03:55,500
HOLD ON A MINUTE, SPIKE.

34
00:03:55,583 --> 00:03:57,416
HEY, I DON'T WANT
TO BOTHER YOU.

35
00:03:57,500 --> 00:03:58,916
DON'T GET SALTY, ALL RIGHT?

36
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:01,500
JUST HOW MUCH DO YOU
KNOW ABOUT THESE BOYS?

37
00:04:01,583 --> 00:04:03,583
ENOUGH TO GET THE PICTURE.

38
00:04:03,666 --> 00:04:04,791
WELL, THEN?

39
00:04:04,875 --> 00:04:06,125
THERE'S A FAT BOUNTY,

40
00:04:06,208 --> 00:04:09,208
PLENTY OF INFO ON THE GUY,
AND WE HAVE A LEAD.

41
00:04:09,291 --> 00:04:11,125
SO WHAT ARE YOU SCARED OF?

42
00:04:11,208 --> 00:04:14,000
SPIKE, YOU'RE AVOIDING
THE SUBJECT, AND YOU KNOW IT.

43
00:04:14,083 --> 00:04:17,375
WHAT ARE TRYING
TO HIDE FROM ME?

44
00:04:17,458 --> 00:04:20,500
SO HOW'D YOU MESS UP
YOUR ARM, HUH, JET?

45
00:04:20,583 --> 00:04:22,541
WHAT DOES THAT
HAVE TO DO WITH IT?

46
00:04:22,625 --> 00:04:23,791
NOTHING AT ALL.

47
00:04:23,875 --> 00:04:26,250
SO WHEN ARE YOU GOING
TO ANSWER MY QUESTION?

48
00:04:26,333 --> 00:04:28,791
WHEN YOU ANSWER MINE.

49
00:04:32,416 --> 00:04:34,375
WHY IS THIS DOOR SO SMALL?

50
00:04:34,458 --> 00:04:36,791
YOU CAN HARDLY GET THROUGH.

51
00:04:39,625 --> 00:04:41,250
UH, WHAT'S GOING ON?

52
00:04:41,333 --> 00:04:42,458
NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS.

53
00:04:42,541 --> 00:04:43,666
HMM. HEY!

54
00:04:43,750 --> 00:04:45,416
WE'RE SUPPOSED TO BE
A TEAM HERE, YOU KNOW.

55
00:04:45,500 --> 00:04:47,375
SINCE WHEN?

56
00:04:47,458 --> 00:04:50,125
YOU'RE JUST WALKING TROUBLE,
SO STAY OUT OF IT.

57
00:04:50,208 --> 00:04:52,500
HMM. FINE.

58
00:04:52,583 --> 00:04:54,208
LIKE I CARE.

59
00:04:54,291 --> 00:04:56,208
SO WHO'S THIS GUY? NEW HIT?

60
00:04:56,291 --> 00:04:57,791
ASK BEFORE YOU LOOK.

61
00:04:57,875 --> 00:04:59,708
IT'S SITTING RIGHT THERE.

62
00:04:59,791 --> 00:05:01,000
LIGHTEN UP.

63
00:05:01,083 --> 00:05:01,916
SPIKE!

64
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:04,208
WAIT A MINUTE, SPIKE!

65
00:05:15,208 --> 00:05:16,458
PREPARE FOR TAKEOFF.

66
00:05:16,541 --> 00:05:18,083
SPIKE! JERK.

67
00:05:18,166 --> 00:05:19,583
I'M NOT GOING TO BACK YOU UP.

68
00:05:19,666 --> 00:05:21,333
YOUR CALL.

69
00:05:28,125 --> 00:05:29,041
DAMN IT!

70
00:05:29,125 --> 00:05:30,583
BULLHEADED.

71
00:05:30,666 --> 00:05:31,916
MAO YENRAI.

72
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:34,916
A 28 MILLION BOUNTY
FOR MURDERING A CRIME BOSS.

73
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:37,541
HE'S THE HEAD
OF A SYNDICATE, HUH?

74
00:05:37,625 --> 00:05:38,416
WHOA!

75
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:40,958
THAT'S WHO YOU GUYS ARE AFTER?

76
00:05:41,708 --> 00:05:43,541
WHAT? YOU HAVE A FIGHT?

77
00:05:43,625 --> 00:05:46,208
CAN IT!
YOU'RE BEING OBNOXIOUS.

78
00:05:46,291 --> 00:05:47,500
HMM. REALLY?

79
00:05:47,583 --> 00:05:49,666
I SAID, CAN IT!

80
00:05:49,750 --> 00:05:53,208
HE CAN DO WHATEVER
THE HELL HE WANTS.

81
00:05:53,291 --> 00:05:56,416
OH, GOD.
MEN ARE SUCH BABIES.

82
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:57,958
HMM?

83
00:06:00,125 --> 00:06:01,000
ARE YOU THERE, JET?

84
00:06:01,083 --> 00:06:02,625
I'VE GOT SOMETHING BIG!

85
00:06:02,708 --> 00:06:04,666
SOMETHING BIG? HMM.

86
00:06:22,375 --> 00:06:24,000
MADAM, EXCUSE ME.

87
00:06:24,083 --> 00:06:27,083
I NEED TO SEE YOUR TICKET
FOR THE CONCERT, PLEASE.

88
00:06:27,166 --> 00:06:27,916
TICKET?

89
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:29,250
OH, I DON'T HAVE ANY TICKET.

90
00:06:29,333 --> 00:06:32,458
WELL, THEN I'M AFRAID
I CAN'T LET YOU IN, MADAM.

91
00:06:32,541 --> 00:06:36,000
ALL RIGHT, BUT HE'S GOING
TO BE VERY UNHAPPY WITH YOU.

92
00:06:36,083 --> 00:06:37,125
HUH?

93
00:06:37,208 --> 00:06:39,833
THAT'S RIGHT, HIM.
BALCONY, FIRST BOX.

94
00:06:39,916 --> 00:06:41,583
YOU KNOW WHO.

95
00:06:41,666 --> 00:06:44,333
OH! MAO YENR--

96
00:06:44,416 --> 00:06:46,375
CAN YOU PARK MY ZIPCRAFT?

97
00:06:46,458 --> 00:06:47,750
IT'S OUT FRONT.

98
00:06:47,833 --> 00:06:48,916
THANKS.

99
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:51,166
OH! MMM.

100
00:06:52,458 --> 00:06:53,666
WHAT MAKES THEM ALL THINK

101
00:06:53,750 --> 00:06:57,041
THEY CAN DO WHATEVER
THE HELL THEY LIKE?

102
00:06:57,125 --> 00:06:58,125
HUH?

103
00:06:58,208 --> 00:07:00,791
THERE'S AN ENCRYPTION
ON THIS THING.

104
00:07:00,875 --> 00:07:02,000
[WHINES]

105
00:07:02,083 --> 00:07:04,041
HMM? YOU WORRIED?

106
00:07:04,125 --> 00:07:05,291
RELAX.

107
00:07:05,375 --> 00:07:08,958
YOU HAVEN'T SEEN
THE DECRYPTION MASTER AT WORK.

108
00:07:09,041 --> 00:07:10,000
YOU SEE?

109
00:07:10,083 --> 00:07:15,041
NOW WE TYPE IN "MAO YENRAI."

110
00:07:15,125 --> 00:07:16,083
SO I WAS RIGHT.

111
00:07:16,166 --> 00:07:17,125
THE BOUNTY'S FOR REAL,

112
00:07:17,208 --> 00:07:20,333
BUT THERE'S A WHOLE LOT
MORE TO IT.

113
00:07:20,416 --> 00:07:24,000
[ORCHESTRA PLAYING]

114
00:07:48,958 --> 00:07:52,666
[MAN SINGING "AVE MARIA"]

115
00:08:02,041 --> 00:08:04,666
IS THIS MR. MAO YENRAI'S BOX?

116
00:08:04,750 --> 00:08:06,708
I LOOKED ALL OVER FOR IT.

117
00:08:06,791 --> 00:08:07,625
ACTUALLY, I--

118
00:08:07,708 --> 00:08:10,083
YES. WE'VE BEEN
WAITING FOR YOU.

119
00:08:10,708 --> 00:08:12,500
[GASPS]

120
00:08:12,583 --> 00:08:14,000
UNH!

121
00:08:14,083 --> 00:08:16,916
WE REQUEST THAT YOU REMAIN
QUIET DURING THE PERFORMANCE.

122
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,916
HMM.

123
00:08:35,666 --> 00:08:37,375
PUT 'EM BACK!

124
00:08:42,083 --> 00:08:44,166
YOU'RE NOT GETTING AWAY!

125
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:50,208
GET OUT OF MY WAY!

126
00:08:50,291 --> 00:08:51,208
HMM?

127
00:08:51,291 --> 00:08:52,416
HUH?

128
00:08:52,500 --> 00:08:54,375
HEY, GIVE IT BACK,
YOU DUMBASS!

129
00:08:54,458 --> 00:08:55,375
GIMME!

130
00:08:55,458 --> 00:08:57,958
OOH.

131
00:08:58,041 --> 00:09:00,125
REALLY! KIDS THESE DAYS!

132
00:09:00,208 --> 00:09:03,833
I'LL HAND YOU BOTH
OVER TO THE POLICE!

133
00:09:05,291 --> 00:09:06,833
OH, MY DEAR GOD.

134
00:09:06,916 --> 00:09:09,458
HEY.

135
00:09:09,541 --> 00:09:11,375
[KIDS GIGGLE]

136
00:09:11,458 --> 00:09:13,250
UH...

137
00:09:14,375 --> 00:09:15,375
ISN'T IT BAD FOR YOUR HEALTH

138
00:09:15,458 --> 00:09:17,833
TO DRINK IT ALL
IN ONE GULP, ANNIE?

139
00:09:17,916 --> 00:09:18,833
WHAT'S BAD FOR MY HEALTH

140
00:09:18,916 --> 00:09:20,583
IS SEEING YOU
COME BACK TO LIFE.

141
00:09:20,666 --> 00:09:21,833
IT'S A SHOCK TO THE SYSTEM.

142
00:09:21,916 --> 00:09:24,375
HEY, THANKS A LOT
FOR THE WARM WELCOME.

143
00:09:24,458 --> 00:09:26,250
HMM! WHY WELCOME THE DEAD?

144
00:09:26,333 --> 00:09:27,416
IT'S ALL FUTILE.

145
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:28,666
BUT I'M ALIVE.

146
00:09:28,750 --> 00:09:31,375
NO, YOU'RE NOT.
YOU DIED 3 YEARS AGO.

147
00:09:31,458 --> 00:09:34,208
THAT'S HOW THINGS WORK HERE.

148
00:09:41,375 --> 00:09:43,666
I KNOW WHY
YOU'RE HERE, SPIKE.

149
00:09:43,750 --> 00:09:45,208
HUH?

150
00:09:45,291 --> 00:09:46,833
YOU WOULDN'T HAVE COME UNLESS
YOU NEEDED SOME INFORMATION,

151
00:09:46,916 --> 00:09:48,250
SOMETHING IMPORTANT, RIGHT?

152
00:09:48,333 --> 00:09:52,750
WELL, I'LL HELP IF I CAN,
BUT DON'T ASK ME TOO MUCH.

153
00:09:52,833 --> 00:09:53,791
ANASTASIA.

154
00:09:53,875 --> 00:09:55,958
NO! DON'T YOU CALL ME THAT!

155
00:09:56,041 --> 00:10:01,208
THERE ARE ONLY TWO PEOPLE
WHO CAN USE THAT NAME.

156
00:10:01,291 --> 00:10:03,791
SO, WHAT DO YOU WANT TO KNOW?

157
00:10:03,875 --> 00:10:08,250
MAO YENRAI,
WHAT HAPPENED TO HIM?

158
00:10:09,750 --> 00:10:13,458
[MAN SINGING "AVE MARIA"]

159
00:10:18,166 --> 00:10:21,791
MAO TAIJIN,
WHAT'S THE REASON FOR THIS?

160
00:10:21,875 --> 00:10:25,083
NO NEED TO SPEAK,
MISS... VALENTINE.

161
00:10:25,166 --> 00:10:26,416
[GASPS]

162
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:29,291
WE'VE DONE A VERY THOROUGH
BACKGROUND CHECK ON YOU.

163
00:10:29,375 --> 00:10:30,750
[GASPS]

164
00:10:30,833 --> 00:10:33,333
REST ASSURED, YOU'LL BE HELD
IN A VERY SECURE LOCATION.

165
00:10:33,416 --> 00:10:35,500
PLEASE, TAKE YOUR SEAT.

166
00:10:35,583 --> 00:10:37,500
OH.

167
00:10:57,125 --> 00:10:58,750
YOU'RE TREMBLING.

168
00:10:58,833 --> 00:11:01,250
WHO ARE YOU?

169
00:11:01,333 --> 00:11:02,958
TELL ME!

170
00:11:05,583 --> 00:11:06,750
VICIOUS.

171
00:11:28,833 --> 00:11:32,416
YOU KNOW, I DON'T
TELL YOU WHAT TO DO,

172
00:11:32,500 --> 00:11:36,750
BUT JUST DON'T GET TANGLED UP
WITH VICIOUS ANYMORE, RIGHT?

173
00:11:36,833 --> 00:11:38,166
WHY AM I TALKING TO YOU?

174
00:11:38,250 --> 00:11:39,250
IT'S USELESS.

175
00:11:39,333 --> 00:11:40,666
SORRY.

176
00:11:40,750 --> 00:11:43,708
YOU'VE NEVER LISTENED
TO ANYONE IN YOUR WHOLE LIFE.

177
00:11:47,541 --> 00:11:50,375
AND ON TOP OF THAT,
YOU'RE A STUBBORN SHOWOFF!

178
00:11:50,458 --> 00:11:51,375
YOU THINK IT'D KILL YOU

179
00:11:51,458 --> 00:11:52,916
TO LISTEN TO YOUR
ELDERS FOR ONCE?

180
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:55,500
NO, THAT'S TOO MUCH TO ASK.

181
00:11:55,583 --> 00:12:00,041
ABOUT MAO, HE HAD A LOT
OF GUYS OUT LOOKING FOR YOU.

182
00:12:00,125 --> 00:12:02,250
HE WAS CONVINCED
YOU WERE STILL ALIVE

183
00:12:02,333 --> 00:12:03,375
SAID HE COULD FEEL IT.

184
00:12:03,458 --> 00:12:05,833
NO ONE COULD
TALK HIM OUT OF IT.

185
00:12:05,916 --> 00:12:10,291
SO NOW HERE YOU ARE,
FINALLY BACK, AND MAO IS...

186
00:12:10,375 --> 00:12:14,291
ANNIE, I THINK
YOU'VE HAD ENOUGH.

187
00:12:14,375 --> 00:12:15,083
NOT YET.

188
00:12:15,166 --> 00:12:17,708
THIS ONE'S FOR MAO.

189
00:12:17,791 --> 00:12:21,541
IF IT'S FOR MAO,
THEN I'LL DRINK IT MYSELF.

190
00:12:43,958 --> 00:12:45,625
ALL RIGHT, AND WHAT
ARE YOU PLANNING

191
00:12:45,708 --> 00:12:46,625
TO DO WITH
ALL THE ARTILLERY?

192
00:12:46,708 --> 00:12:48,500
WHERE'S THE GIRL?

193
00:12:48,583 --> 00:12:49,875
WHEN SHE SAW THE BOUNTY FIGURE,

194
00:12:49,958 --> 00:12:51,666
SHE HAD A LAPSE OF SANITY.

195
00:12:51,750 --> 00:12:53,041
I'M SURE SHE'S OUT SOMEWHERE

196
00:12:53,125 --> 00:12:55,458
SCREWING UP
AND GETTING IN TROUBLE.

197
00:12:55,541 --> 00:12:56,458
I SEE.

198
00:12:56,541 --> 00:12:57,791
LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING.

199
00:12:57,875 --> 00:12:59,833
YOU'RE NOT GOING TO GET
ANY REWARD MONEY FOR MAO.

200
00:12:59,916 --> 00:13:02,750
HE'S ALREADY DEAD...
ASSASSINATED.

201
00:13:02,833 --> 00:13:07,125
INTERNAL POLITICS BETWEEN
RIVAL CRIME SYNDICATES,

202
00:13:07,208 --> 00:13:08,208
YOU UNDERSTAND?

203
00:13:08,291 --> 00:13:09,125
IT'S A TRAP!

204
00:13:09,208 --> 00:13:10,083
YEAH, I KNOW.

205
00:13:10,166 --> 00:13:11,916
I KNOW THE WHOLE SAD STORY.

206
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:14,458
AND YOU'RE STILL GOING?

207
00:13:14,541 --> 00:13:16,875
WAIT. DOES THIS
HAVE TO DO WITH MAO?

208
00:13:16,958 --> 00:13:19,958
YEAH. I HAVE
A DEBT TO PAY OFF.

209
00:13:22,375 --> 00:13:25,333
YOU WANTED TO KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED TO MY ARM.

210
00:13:25,416 --> 00:13:26,208
HUH?

211
00:13:26,291 --> 00:13:27,708
THIS IS WHAT I PAID,

212
00:13:27,791 --> 00:13:30,916
YEAH, FOR BEING TOO GUNGHO
AND RUNNING AHEAD OF THE GAME.

213
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:31,958
YOU GET THE POINT?

214
00:13:32,041 --> 00:13:34,041
I DON'T WANT
TO DO THIS, JET.

215
00:13:34,125 --> 00:13:35,291
THEN WHY ARE YOU?

216
00:13:35,375 --> 00:13:38,916
LET'S JUST SAY MY PAST
IS CATCHING UP TO ME.

217
00:13:40,166 --> 00:13:41,750
[BEEPING]

218
00:13:44,333 --> 00:13:46,375
I KIND OF GOT MYSELF CAUGHT.

219
00:13:46,458 --> 00:13:47,583
WHA--?

220
00:13:47,666 --> 00:13:49,208
YEAH. THEY WANT YOU
TO COME AND PICK ME UP.

221
00:13:49,291 --> 00:13:51,958
EITHER YOU SHOW UP
AT THE PLACE THEY SPECIFY,

222
00:13:52,041 --> 00:13:53,833
OR MY LIFE IS OVER.

223
00:13:53,916 --> 00:13:55,125
OH, THE ARRIVAL TIME IS--

224
00:13:55,208 --> 00:13:56,958
WHO ASKED YOU
TO GO OFF ON YOUR OWN?

225
00:13:57,041 --> 00:13:58,958
AW, COME ON, NOW!

226
00:13:59,041 --> 00:14:00,458
WE'RE COMRADES, RIGHT?

227
00:14:00,541 --> 00:14:03,541
YOU BROUGHT THIS ON YOURSELF,
SO DEAL WITH IT YOURSELF.

228
00:14:03,625 --> 00:14:04,666
WE'RE BUSY.

229
00:14:04,750 --> 00:14:05,666
NO! WAIT, JET!

230
00:14:05,750 --> 00:14:07,666
--HUH?
--WHERE ARE YOU?

231
00:14:07,750 --> 00:14:08,916
HUH?

232
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:10,958
YOU MEAN YOU'RE REALLY
GOING TO COME FOR ME?

233
00:14:11,041 --> 00:14:12,250
WELL, IT'S POSSIBLE.

234
00:14:12,333 --> 00:14:14,833
I'VE GOT MY REASONS,
SO DON'T TAKE IT PERSONAL.

235
00:14:14,916 --> 00:14:16,250
SPIKE!

236
00:14:23,666 --> 00:14:26,291
♪ I DON'T FEEL A THING ♪

237
00:14:26,375 --> 00:14:29,416
♪ AND I STOPPED REMEMBERING ♪

238
00:14:29,500 --> 00:14:36,916
♪ THE DAYS ARE JUST LIKE
MOMENTS TURNED TO HOURS ♪

239
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:39,583
♪ MOTHER USED TO SAY ♪

240
00:14:39,666 --> 00:14:41,875
♪ IF YOU WANT,
YOU'LL FIND A WAY ♪

241
00:14:41,958 --> 00:14:49,916
♪ BUT MOTHER NEVER DANCED
THROUGH FIRE SHOWERS ♪

242
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:55,833
♪ WALK IN THE RAIN ♪

243
00:14:55,916 --> 00:14:58,958
♪ IN THE RAIN ♪

244
00:14:59,041 --> 00:15:02,500
♪ IN THE RAIN ♪

245
00:15:02,583 --> 00:15:05,833
♪ I WALK IN THE RAIN ♪

246
00:15:05,916 --> 00:15:09,000
♪ IN THE RAIN ♪

247
00:15:09,083 --> 00:15:13,166
♪ IS IT RIGHT ♪

